column41: I don't like the date picker. If I'm entering a birthdate I'd have to click too many times to get it to the right year. The font was also weird. December looked like Deoember. The c looked like an o. Als the text associated with the fields is centered between the fields. It should be more closely associated (proximity) with the field it belongs to. Bad spacing for some of the text elements e.g. Tax file number(TFN) is missing a space between the "r(" Some labels (Title) were bold and the rest were not. The buttons lacked any affordance for 'clickability' this whole "flat UI" trend has jumped the shark. It's taking us back to the 1980's where we had very few graphic options. At the end of adding info for one employee, the "Employees.............................................................................Add+" function is at the top, instead of at the bottom where it needs to be. It should also be a proper green button instead of a black button built into a header bar. Was the name of the calculator really the most obvious plain language name you could come up with?

Is this different then the grey "Generate SGC statement"? If so, why?
